Explanation:

The text mentions that the Zwickauer Mulde has two source rivers, the Red Mulde and the White Mulde. Both of these source rivers empty into the Muldenberg valley dammed reservoir after approx. 3 km. Then, it says that the Zwickauer Mulde emerges from this reservoir and flows to Eibenstock, where it empties into the largest reservoir in Saxony, the Eibenstock dam.

This suggests that the Zwickau Mulde does indeed feed into the Eibenstock Dam. Therefore, the answer is "yes".
